  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Pacific Adaptation through Labour Mobility in the Low-Lying Atoll States of Kiribati, the Marshall Islands and Tuvalu</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Data gaps limit the capacity of governments to develop evidence-based labor mobility (LM) programmes. To address this gap, this project will begin by gathering new data relating to LM and labour markets in three Pacific countries which are vulnerable to climate change:  Marshall Islands (RMI), Kiribati, and Tuvalu. Following data collection, IOM will work with Kiribati and Tuvalu to use this data to feed into national labour market information systems (LMIS). IOM will organise two training sessions (Tuvalu and Kiribati) that will end with a roundtable to agree on next steps for the roll-out of LM activities in-country. RMI does not have an NLMP in place, however this is a priority for the government moving forward. IOM will organise a national dissemination and planning workshop at which the LM research report will be launched and findings analysed, following which an action plan for developing the NLMP and implementing policy recommendations within the report will be developed.</narrative>
  </description>
